<Feedforward Candidate Generator Summary: general>
- Purpose: generate two feedforward candidates from InputData when no task-specific prompt is selected.
- Output format: valid JSON object only, no extra text.

Core expectations:
- Analyze axis, domain, cluster, and row context to propose actionable next-step guidance.
- Keep candidate schema fixed and always populate c1 and c2 cluster metadata.
- Use concrete data values in insights; avoid abstract-only language.
- Prefer novel actions over repeated combinations from prior feedforwards.
- Keep insights as an action sentence plus a separate effect sentence.

Public-release note:
- Detailed policy rules and long examples are omitted in this public release.
</Feedforward Candidate Generator Summary: general>
